President Biden and Vice President Harris have announced that the application period for the Spring session of the White House Internship Program will open on Monday, July 24th. The session will begin in January 2024. This program is a public service leadership and development program that offers paid internships across the Executive Office of the President. Participants must be U.S. citizens, at least 18 years old, and meet certain criteria. The application period will close on Friday, August 18th. Interested candidates can find the online application and more information at WH.gov/intern. Questions can be directed to the White House Internship Program team at internship@who.eop.gov.